<br>
I use SoD and red epic (100 dd + 500 hate proc). I can't back this up in a scientific way, but SoD certainly feels like more aggro (or at least as much as) than the red epic (proc vs proc). Granted the driver's proc can't be resisted and SoD's can, but 1. Resists still seem to generate considerable aggro.. not as much as when they land, but certainly a good amount of aggro. 2. SoD's proc is rarely resisted except by mobs with extremely high magic resist. However, even in such cases anarchy will often land for a low amount of damage (say 1-100). <br>
<br>
No SoD is not the be all end all weapon anymore, but I'd still consider it rather nice (especially for those of us who are a long way off from going to the elemental planes or something).<br>
